messages.speech:
Students can submit a copy of their ACT score report (with name and date on document) INSTEAD of taking the ACCUPLACER Course Placement Test, if students meet the following scores:

    Reading: 21 or higher
    Mathematics: 22 or higher

A student may substitute a subject of the ACT for a corresponding subject of ACCUPLACER Course Placement Test, if only that subject area meets the ACT score requirement. The student must then take the remaining subjects via ACCUPLACER Course Placement Test.
